data.content:
noun
plural -nas
[count] a thin usually green layer that forms naturally on the metals copper and bronze when they are exposed to the air for a long time
a shiny or dark surface that forms naturally on something (such as wood or leather) that is used for a long time - usually singular
the beautiful patina of this antique table
a thin layer - usually singular
The kitchen counter was covered with a patina of grease. - often used figuratively
a criminal who has been given a patina of respectability by his friendship with well-known businessmen
